premise_source_doc_sentence: Glenne Aimee Headly  (  born March 13 , 1955  )  is an American actress .
She is known for her roles in Dirty Rotten Scoundrels and Mr. Holland 's Opus .
Headly has received Theatre World Awards and four Joseph Jefferson Awards , and was nominated for two Primetime Emmy Awards .
Most recently , Headly and Ed Begley Jr. have been tapped for lead roles opposite Josh Hutcherson in Future Man , Hulu 's half-hour comedy pilot from Seth Rogen and Evan Goldberg .
It was directed by Alan Rudolph and stars Demi Moore , Glenne Headly , Bruce Willis , and Harvey Keitel .
The cast features Craig Wasson , Jodi Thelen , Jim Metzler and Glenne Headly .

Warren Beatty produced , directed , and starred in the film , which features supporting roles from Al Pacino , Charles Durning , Madonna , Dustin Hoffman , William Forsythe , Glenne Headly , Paul Sorvino , Dick Van Dyke , and Charlie Korsmo .

The film won an Emmy Award for Outstanding Casting for a Miniseries or a Special  (  Linda Lowy  )  and was nominated for Outstanding Directing for a Miniseries or a Special  (  Anjelica Huston  )  , Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Miniseries or a Special  (  Glenne Headly  )  , and Outstanding Made for Television Movie  (  Amanda DiGiulio , Gary Hoffman  )  .
Dirty Rotten Scoundrels is a 1988 American comedy film directed by Frank Oz and starring Steve Martin , Michael Caine and Glenne Headly .
